  "poem": {
    "content": "I long to give myself permission,\nto travel past this dusty frame.\n\nThe inner hum a faulty stereo,\na cheap refrain I can't erase.\n\nEnter the census taker's world,\na clerk describes my barren state.\n\nI draw a leopard on the wall,\na truth projected, fierce and bold.\n\nA fruit hangs heavy, bittersweet,\nutility undefined, untold.\n\nThis aching want, this hollow cast,\nI see reflections, shadows deep.\n\nI travel there, to find the core,\nwhere ancient secrets softly sleep.\n\nThe leopard roars, a vibrant call,\nto draw you in, past barren wall.\n\nThe fruit I give, a ripened gift,\nto understand the inner shift.\n\nTo find our truth within the roar,\nto travel inward, evermore.",
